  "prompt": "How do I delete my gmail only from one device and retain the same on other devices?",
  "response": "To delete your Gmail account from one device while retaining it on others, you need to remove the Gmail app or account from that specific device without affecting the settings on your other devices. Here\u2019s how to do it based on the type of device you're using:\n\n### For Android Devices\n\n1. **Open the Settings app** on your phone or tablet.\n2. Scroll down and select **Accounts** or **Users & accounts**.\n3. Find and select your **Google** account (the one associated with Gmail).\n4. Tap on **Remove account**. This will delete the account from your device but will not delete it from Google or other devices.\n\n### For iOS Devices (iPhone/iPad)\n\n1. **Open the Settings app** on your iOS device.\n2. Scroll down and tap on **Mail** (or **Passwords & Accounts** in some versions).\n3. Select **Accounts** and then tap on the Gmail account you want to remove.\n4. Tap on **Delete Account** and confirm. This removes the account from that device only.\n\n### For Web Browsers (if you don't want your email saved in the browser)\n\n1. If you're using a web browser, simply log out of your Gmail account by clicking on your profile picture in the top right corner and selecting **Sign out**.\n2. To ensure that all cookies and cache related to your account are removed, you can clear the browser cache or use an incognito/private browsing window.\n\n### Notes:\n- Removing your Gmail account from a device will not delete any emails or data from your Google account; they will still be accessible when you log in from another device or via the web.\n- If you are using a third-party mail app, the steps might be slightly different. Look for the account settings in that specific app to remove the Gmail account.\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively delete your Gmail from a single device while keeping it active on your other devices.",
